TO LOGIN from LINUX COMMAND LINE:
mysql -u username -p

AFTER YOU ARE LOGGED IN AND HAVE A: mysql>

show databases;
show tables from DATABASENAME;

TO ENABLE ACCESS ACCROSS NETWORK:

GRANT ALL ON *.* TO DATABASEUSERNAME@'IPADDRESS' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
DONT REMOVE THE QUOTES....

Querey Skelton:
SELECT FEILDNAME
FROM TABLENAME
WHERE SOMESORTOFFILTER

Example:
To show the first and last name, email address and store id of customers of store ID 2 ONLY the following query would be ran:

SELECT first_name,last_name, email, store_id
FROM customer
WHERE store_id = 2
